oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Pvt. Mack Bennett with his mother, Mary Angeline Edwards Bennett
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Picture of Pvt. Mack Mitchell Bennett (1892-1951) who served in Btry. F, 318th FA Regt., 81st Div. during World War I. He is pictured with his mother, Mary Angeline Edwards Bennett. Inscribed on the back of the photograph"must have been taken in the early twentys Mack and Mother dont know where they were standing. Mack Bennett and his mother, Mary Angeline (Edwards) Bennett"
